Holotype : Total body length 720 m (
Fig. 1
). Body white or transparent. Cuticle smooth. Eyes absent. Buccopharyngeal tube 76 m long and 3 m wide. Apophyses for insertion of stylet muscles very wide, with a flat ridge. Drop­like thickening between buccal and pharyngeal tube absent. Buccal tube 39 m long. Pharyngeal tube with spiral thickening 37 m long, ending (on dorsal or ventral view) with semilunar structures ( 4 m long). In pharynx, between end of pharyngeal tube and the first macroplacoid two very slender cuticular bars directed forward ( 5 m long). Stylet supports inserted 1 m above upper limit of pharyngeal tube. Pharyngeal bulb pear­shaped, 77 m long and 37 m wide, containing two slender, lancet­shaped macroplacoids with irregularly undulated edges. First macroplacoid 14 m , second 33 m long; both 1 m wide. Macroplacoid row 48 m long. Septulae and microplacoid absent (
Figs 2­3
). Claws of
Hypsibius
­ type ; on I pair of legs: external (primary branch: 30 m , secondary: 13 m ), internal (pb.: 17 m , sb.: 10 m ); II: ext. (pb.: 33 m , sb.: 15 m ), int. (pb.: 20 m , sb.: 12 m ); III: ext. (pb.: 34 m , sb.: 14 m ), int. (pb.: 22 m , sb.: 12 m ); VI: ext. (pb.: 34 m , sb.: 16 m ), int. (pb.: 23 m , sb.: 14 m ). Primary branches of internal and external claws with two accessory points. On IV pair of legs lunules with fine teeth. Cuticular bars on legs absent (
Figs 4­5
). Eggs unknown.

Northern Mongolia ; Archangaj Ajmag, Tehijn Cagan Nuur National Park; Tarbagataj Mts.; 2700 m ; mosses from rocks;
VII 2000
; leg. oe. Kaczmarek.
